ican Cancer Society]]\n|}\n\n====Archival footage====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Director\n! Studio\n|-\n| 1964 || ''[[Four Days in November]]'' || Herself || [[Mel Stuart]] || [[United Artists]]\n|-\n| 1964 || ''MGM's Big Parade of Comedy''<ref>a.k.a. ''The Big Parade of Comedy''</ref> || Herself<ref name=\"archival\">Archival footage</ref> || [[Robert Youngson]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1974 ||''[[That's Entertainment!]]'' || Janie Barlow (''[[Dancing Lady]]'')<ref name=\"archival\" /> || [[Jack Haley Jr.]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1984 || ''[[Terror in the Aisles]]'' || Blanche Hudson (''[[What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (film)|What Ever Happened to Baby Jane?]]'')<ref name=\"archival\" /> || [[Andrew J. Kuehn]] || [[Universal Pictures|Universal]]\n|-\n| 1985 || ''[[That's Dancing!]]'' || Herself<ref name=\"archival\" /> || [[Jack Haley Jr.]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1994 || ''[[That's Entertainment! III]]'' || Jenny Stewart (''[[Torch Song (1953 film)|Torch Song]]'')<ref name=\"archival\" /> || Bud Friedgen, Michael J. Sheridan || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|}\n\n====Uncompleted films====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Director\n! Studio\n|-\n| 1929 || ''[[Tide of Empire]]'' || Josephita (replaced by [[Ren\u00e9e Ador\u00e9e]]) || [[Allan Dwan]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1930 || ''[[Great Day (unfinished film)|Great Day]]'' || Susie Totheridge || [[Harry Beaumont]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1930 || ''[[The March of Time (film)|The March of Time]]'' || Herself || [[Charles Reisner]] || [[Metro-Goldwyn-Mayer]]\n|-\n| 1964 || ''[[Hush...Hush, Sweet Charlotte]]'' || Miriam Deering (replaced by [[Olivia de Havilland]] due to illness) || [[Robert Aldrich]] || [[20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox]]\n|}\n\n====Box-office ranking====\nFor a number of years, Crawford was regularly voted as one of the top money-making stars in the country in [[Top Ten Money Making Stars Poll|the annual ''Quigley'' Poll]]:<ref>[http://www.quigleypublishing.com/MPalmanac/Top10/Top10_lists.html Top Ten Money Making Stars] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141221063625/http://www.quigleypublishing.com/MPalmanac/Top10/Top10_lists.html |date=2014-12-21 }}</ref>\n*1930 \u2013 1st\n*1931 \u2013 3rd\n*1932 \u2013 3rd\n*1933 \u2013 10th\n*1934 \u2013 6th\n*1935 \u2013 5th\n*1936 \u2013 7th\n*1937 \u2013 16th\n*1947 \u2013 21st\n\n===Television===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Episode\n! Director\n! Network\n|-\n| 1953 || ''[[The Revlon Mirror Theater]]'' || Margaret Hughes || \"Because I Love Him\" || [[Rod Amateau]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1954 || ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' || Mary Andrews || \"The Road to Edinburgh\" || [[Rod Amateau]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1958 || ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' || Ruth Marshall || \"Strange Witness\" || [[Herschel Daugherty]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''The Joan Crawford Show''<ref>TV pilot for ''The Joan Crawford Show'' unsold series</ref> || Susan Conrad || \"Woman on the Run\" || [[Dick Powell]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[General Electric Theater]]'' || Ann Howard || \"And One Was Loyal\" || [[Herschel Daugherty]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[The Joseph Cotten Show]]'' || Ruth Marshall || \"Strange Witness\" || [[Herschel Daugherty]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1959 || ''[[Dick Powell's Zane Grey Theatre|Zane Grey Theatre]]'' || Stella Faring || \"Rebel Range\" || [[Don Medford]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1961 || ''[[Dick Powell's Zane Grey Theatre|Zane Grey Theatre]]'' || Sarah and Melanie Hobbes || \"One Must Die\" || [[Lewis Allen (director)|Lewis Allen]] || [[CBS]]\n|-\n| 1961 || ''[[The DuPont Show of the Week]]'' || Hostess || \"The Ziegfeld Touch\" || James Elson || [[NBC]]\n|-\n| 1963 || ''[[Route 66 (TV series)|Route 66]]'' || Morgan Matheson Harper || \"[[List of Route 66 episodes|Same Picture, Different Frame]]\" || [[Philip L