{"title_page": "Hundred of Strathalbyn", "text_new": "{{Use Australian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox Australian place\n| type=cadastral\n| name= Hundred of Strathalbyn\n| state = sa\n| image              = \n| image_upright      = \n| caption            = \n| image_alt          = \n| coordinates        = {{Coord|35.20|S|138.95|E|display=inline,title}}\n| coord_ref          = \n| established        = {{start date|1850|12|12}}\n| area               = {{convert|83|mi2}}\n| area_footnotes     = <ref name=\"PLB\">{{cite web |url=http://maps.sa.gov.au/plb/ |title=Placename Details: Hundred of Strathalbyn |work=Property Location Browser Report |id=SA0064831 |publisher=[[Government of South Australia]] |date=29 January 2009 |accessdate=31 January 2019}}</ref>\n| lga                = Alexandrina Council\n| region             = \n| county             = County of Hindmarsh\n| hundred            = Strathalbyn\n| near-nw            = [[Hundred of Macclesfield|Macclesfield]]\n| near-n             = [[Hundred of Kanmantoo|Kanmantoo]]\n| near-ne            = [[Hundred of Monarto|Monarto]]\n| near-e             = [[Hundred of Freeling|Freeling]]\n| near-se            = [[Hundred of Freeling|Freeling]]\n| near-s             = [[Hundred of Bremer|Bremer]]\n| near-sw            = [[Hundred of Kondoparinga|Kondoparinga]]\n| near-w             = [[Hundred of Macclesfield|Macclesfield]]\n}}\nThe '''Hundred of Strathalbyn''' is a cadastral division of the [[County of Hindmarsh]] in [[South Australia]]. It lies west of the [[Adelaide Hills]] and east of [[Lake Alexandrina (South Australia)|Lake Alexandrina]] and includes at its southwestern extremity the town of [[Strathalbyn, South Australia|Strathalbyn]]. Its name is derived from that used for a sub-division granted in 1841. No definitive derivation for the subdivision of Strathalbyn name is known but it is deemed probable that [[John Rankine (politician)|John Rankine]] or his brother William provided the name with the meaning given as \"white valley\" from the [[Scottish Gaelic|Scottish]] ''[[strath|srath]]'' and ''[[Albion#Etymology|albion]]''.<ref name=\"PLBtown\">{{cite web |url=http://maps.sa.gov.au/plb/ |title=Placename Details: Strathalbyn |work=Property Location Browser Report |id=SA0064818 |publisher=[[Government of South Australia]] |date=4 July 2008 |accessdate=31 January 2019 |quote=On 16 November 1841 William Rankine and James Dawson received the land grant of Section 2600 and shortly thereafter subdivided it, the first sale of allotments being registered on 10 January 1844. Various views as to origin of name. Possible named by Rankine brothers in 1839 with the meaning give as 'white valley' as the Scottish 'strath' was suggested by the resemblance & 'albion' 'white'. Private subdivision of same name over sec 2745, Hundred of Bremer. Includes prior named private subdivisions of Strathalbyn, Strathalbyn Extension, Strathalbyn North, Strathalbyn South, Strathalbyn East and Strathalbyn West. Boundaries created in August 2000 for long established name. The Surveyor-General approved the exclusion of a portion of Macclesfield and inclusion into Strathalbyn on the 29/5/2008, the change was gazetted on 3/7/2008.}}</ref> Mount Barker Creek forms much of the northern hundred boundary while the [[Bremer River (South Australia)|Bremer River]] forms the eastern border.\n\n[[File:Hundred of Strathalbyn, 1964 (23417052759).jpg|thumb|left|Plan of the Hundred of Strathalbyn in 1964]]\n\nThe localities of [[Highland Valley, South Australia|Highland Valley]], [[Red Creek, South Australia|Red Creek]], [[Salem, South Australia|Salem]] and the township of [[Woodchester, South Australia|Woodchester]] are also within the hundred along with parts of [[Belvidere, South Australia (Alexandrina)|Belvidere]], [[Bletchley, South Australia|Bletchley]], [[Gemmells, South Australia|Gemmells]], [[Hartley, South Australia|Hartley]], and [[Langhorne Creek, South Australia|Langhorne Creek]]. Parts of the [[Bugle Ranges, South Australia|Bugle Ranges]], [[Mount Barker, South Australia|Mount Barker]], [[Mount Barker Springs, South Australia|Mount Barker Springs]], [[Petwood, South Australia|Petwood]] and [[Wistow, South Australia|Wistow]] localities also overlap the northwestern part of the hundred.<ref name=\"PLB\"/>\n\n==Local government==\nThe [[District Council of Strathalbyn]] was established within the south of the hundred in 1854. The [[Corporated Town of Strathalbyn]] seceded in 1868 to formed dedicated local government for the township until it re-amalgamated with the district council in 1976.<ref name=\"CivicRecord1986\">{{Citation |last=Matthews |first=Penny |title=South Australia, the civic record, 1836\u20131986 |publication-date=1986 |publisher=Wakefield Press |isbn=978-0-949268-82-2 |pages=562}}</ref> In 1997 the Strathalbyn council was dissolved and absorbed into the new and much larger [[Alexandrina Council]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Hundreds of South Australia}}\n\n[[Category:Hundreds of South Australia|Strathalbyn]]\n[[Category:1850 establishments in Australia]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use Australian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox Australian place\n| type=cadastral\n| name= Hundred of Strathalbyn\n| state = sa\n| image              = \n| image_upright      = \n| caption            = \n| image_alt          = \n| coordinates        = {{Coord|35.20|S|138.95|E|display=inline,title}}\n| coord_ref          = \n| established        = {{start date|1850|12|12}}\n| area               = {{convert|83|mi2}}\n| area_footnotes     = <ref name=\"PLB\">{{cite web |url=http://maps.sa.gov.au/plb/ |title=Placename Details: Hundred of Strathalbyn |work=Property Location Browser Report |id=SA0064831 |publisher=[[Government of South Australia]] |date=29 January 2009 |accessdate=31 January 2019}}</ref>\n| lga                = Alexandrina Council\n| region             = \n| county             = County of Hindmarsh\n| hundred            = Strathalbyn\n| near-nw            = [[Hundred of Macclesfield|Macclesfield]]\n| near-n             = [[Hundred of Kanmantoo|Kanmantoo]]\n| near-ne            = [[Hundred of Monarto|Monarto]]\n| near-e             = [[Hundred of Freeling|Freeling]]\n| near-se            = [[Hundred of Freeling|Freeling]]\n| near-s             = [[Hundred of Bremer|Bremer]]\n| near-sw            = [[Hundred of Kondoparinga|Kondoparinga]]\n| near-w             = [[Hundred of Macclesfield|Macclesfield]]\n}}\nThe '''Hundred of Strathalbyn''' is a cadastral division of the [[County of Hindmarsh]] in [[South Australia]]. It lies west of the [[Adelaide Hills]] and east of [[Lake Alexandrina (South Australia)|Lake Alexandrina]] and includes at its southwestern extremity the town of [[Strathalbyn, South Australia|Strathalbyn]]. Its name is derived from that used for a sub-division granted in 1841. No definitive derivation for the subdivision of Strathalbyn name is known but it is deemed probable that [[John Rankine (politician)|John Rankine]] or his brother William provided the name with the meaning given as \"white valley\" from the [[Scottish Gaelic|Scottish]] ''[[strath|srath]]'' and ''[[Albion#Etymology|albion]]''.<ref name=\"PLBtown\">{{cite web |url=http://maps.sa.gov.au/plb/ |title=Placename Details: Strathalbyn |work=Property Location Browser Report |id=SA0064818 |publisher=[[Government of South Australia]] |date=4 July 2008 |accessdate=31 January 2019 |quote=On 16 November 1841 William Rankine and James Dawson received the land grant of Section 2600 and shortly thereafter subdivided it, the first sale of allotments being registered on 10 January 1844. Various views as to origin of name. Possible named by Rankine brothers in 1839 with the meaning give as 'white valley' as the Scottish 'strath' was suggested by the resemblance & 'albion' 'white'. Private subdivision of same name over sec 2745, Hundred of Bremer. Includes prior named private subdivisions of Strathalbyn, Strathalbyn Extension, Strathalbyn North, Strathalbyn South, Strathalbyn East and Strathalbyn West. Boundaries created in August 2000 for long established name. The Surveyor-General approved the exclusion of a portion of Macclesfield and inclusion into Strathalbyn on the 29/5/2008, the change was gazetted on 3/7/2008.}}</ref> Mount Barker Creek forms much of the northern hundred boundary while the [[Bremer River (South Australia)|Bremer River]] forms the eastern border.\n\n[[File:Hundred of Strathalbyn, 1964 (23417052759).jpg|thumb|left|Plan of the Hundred of Strathalbyn in 1964]]\n\nThe localities of [[Highland Valley, South Australia|Highland Valley]], [[Red Creek, South Australia|Red Creek]], [[Salem, South Australia|Salem]] and the township of [[Woodchester, South Australia|Woodchester]] are also within the hundred along with parts of [[Belvidere, South Australia (Alexandrina)|Belvidere]], [[Bletchley, South Australia|Bletchley]], [[Gemmells, South Australia|Gemmells]], [[Hartley, South Australia|Hartley]], and [[Langhorne Creek, South Australia|Langhorne Creek]]. Parts of the [[Bugle Ranges, South Australia|Bugle Ranges]], [[Mount Barker, South Australia|Mount Barker]], [[Mount Barker Springs, South Australia|Mount Barker Springs]], [[Petwood, South Australia|Petwood]] and [[Wistow, South Australia|Wistow]] localites also overlap the northwestern part of the hundred.<ref name=\"PLB\"/>\n\n==Local government==\nThe [[District Council of Strathalbyn]] was established within the south of the hundred in 1854. The [[Corporated Town of Strathalbyn]] seceded in 1868 to formed dedicated local government for the township until it re-amalgamated with the district council in 1976.<ref name=\"CivicRecord1986\">{{Citation |last=Matthews |first=Penny |title=South Australia, the civic record, 1836\u20131986 |publication-date=1986 |publisher=Wakefield Press |isbn=978-0-949268-82-2 |pages=562}}</ref> In 1997 the Strathalbyn council was dissolved and absorbed into the new and much larger [[Alexandrina Council]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Hundreds of South Australia}}\n\n[[Category:Hundreds of South Australia|Strathalbyn]]\n[[Category:1850 establishments in Australia]]\n", "name_user": "WereSpielChequers", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Typo fixing, replaced: localites \u2192 localities", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hundred_of_Strathalbyn"}
